<HEADLINE>
FT  29 SEP 93 / International Capital Markets: Midland Bank issues first
preferred stock
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TRACY CORRIGAN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MIDLAND Bank, the UK clearing bank owned by HSBC Holdings, yesterday
launched its first offering of preferred stock, which counts as Tier 1
capital under Basle capital adequacy rules, writes Tracy Corrigan. The
offering consists of a Dollars 250m issue of non-cumulative preference
shares, arranged by Merrill Lynch and placed with US retail investors.
Midland is well-capitalised with a total capital ratio of 11.4 per cent as
at June 30 - well above the 8 per cent minimum requirement - of which 6.5
per cent is Tier 1 capital. However, all of Midland's existing Tier 1
capital is denominated in sterling and the bank has substantial dollar
assets.
