<DATELINE>
   WASHINGTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
MARRIOTT Corporation, the US lodging and food services group, has received a
favourable ruling from the US Internal Revenue Service that the planned
spin-off of its lodging and services management operations as Marriott
International will be tax-free, Reuter reports from Washington.
The company said the spin-off had been dependent on a favourable IRS ruling,
among other conditions, and should its board at a September 29 meeting find
that all conditions had been met, the distribution of one Marriott
International share for each Marriott Corp share held would be made on
October 8 to holders of record on September 30.
After the spin-off, which is taking the form of a special dividend, Marriott
will change its name to Host Marriott.
The associated exchange offer for its outstanding notes and senior
debentures is scheduled to expire on October 7.
