shareholder of Kendall Square Research, a supercomputer company.
He said he had retained International Creative Management (ICM), the
Hollywood talent agency, and its chairman to advise him.
Credit Lyonnais took control of MGM last year after foreclosing on loans it
made to Mr Giancarlo Parretti, an Italian entrepreneur who bought the
company in 1990 from Mr Kirk Kerkorian for Dollars 1.3bn. Credit Lyonnais is
involved in litigation with Mr Kerkorian.
Under US banking law Credit Lyonnais must sell the studio by 1997.
