<HEADLINE>
FT  29 SEP 93 / International Company News: Vontobel takes stake in Swiss
bank
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By FRANCIS WILLIAMS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   GENEVA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
VONTOBEL Holding, the Zurich-based private banking group, has taken an
agreed one-third stake in Tardy, de Watteville &amp; Cie, a small Geneva private
bank. It plans to raise its share to two-thirds within two years. The price
paid - in cash and shares - was not disclosed.
The move represents a first step along the path mapped out last May by Mr
Hans-Dieter Vontobel, chairman of Vontobel Holding, to ensure an independent
future for the family-controlled group.
The three existing partners of Tardy, de Watteville will continue to run the
Geneva bank, which employs 55 people and had a balance sheet of SFr94m
(Dollars 64.9m) at the end of July. One partner, Mr Bernard de Watteville,
is to be proposed to the Vontobel board.
</TEXT>
