<HEADLINE>
FT  29 SEP 93 / International Company News: Kerry raises Dollars 155m to cut
US debt
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TIM COONE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   DUBLIN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
KERRY GROUP, the international dairy products and foods company based in
Ireland, has raised Dollars 155m (Pounds 101m) in its first private placing
of senior loan notes with US investors, with a view to reducing debt charges
in its US operations.
The placement is split into two nearly equal tranches with maturities of
seven and 10 years, and carries a fixed, but undisclosed, interest rate.
The company's approach to US capital markets aimed to take advantage of both
attractive rates and what it described as keen investor appetites for
investment-grade corporate issues.
The funds will facilitate a total restructuring of Kerry's current
indebtedness in the US.
A small portion will remain to finance further acquisitions, but total group
debt at the year-end will not be significantly greater than the IPounds 109m
(Pounds 104m) at the end of 1992.
The company has also acquired Research Foods, a subsidiary of F&amp;C
International of the US, for CDollars 10m (Pounds 5m). This is the second
acquisition of a food ingredients company in Canada by Kerry this year, the
first being Malcolm Foods last March.
The combined turnover of the two subsidiaries will be approximately CDollars
30m, and will give Kerry a 50 per cent share of the specialist snack food
ingredients business in Canada.
The company is also looking at several acquisition options in Mexico as the
development of the Nafta agreement gives opportunities for expansion in both
Mexico and South America.
</TEXT>
