<HEADLINE>
FT  29 SEP 93 / UK Company News: Amberley makes Pounds 6m purchase
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
AMBERLEY Group, the USM-quoted building services concern, has made the first
move in its intended growth by acquisition with the purchase of Lawrence
Industries. It is also raising Pounds 6.7m net through a placing and open
offer.
It is paying a maximum of Pounds 6.27m, of which Pounds 200,000 is dependent
on net asset value and Pounds 700,000 profit-related. The initial payment of
Pounds 5.27m will be satisfied by Pounds 4.19m cash and the balance in the
shares.
Lawrence, an importer of processed mineral and fibre products, achieved
pre-tax profits of Pounds 291,000 on turnover of Pounds 952,000 in the four
months to July 31 having reported Pounds 697,000 profits on Pounds 2.16m
turnover in the previous nine months.
The placing is of 17.6m shares at 38p, of which 6.44m is being offered to
shareholders on a 1-for-1 basis. The proceeds will be used for the initial
cash payment, with the rest used for expenses of the purchase and reducing
borrowings.
