<HEADLINE>
FT  29 SEP 93 / UK Company News: Thorn issues Rent-a-Center denial
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Thorn EMI yesterday issued a statement through the Stock Exchange accusing
the Wall Street Journal of publishing a 'seriously misleading' article about
the group's US rental business.
The article, which appeared last week, alleged that staff at Thorn's
Rent-a-Center subsidiary employed strong-arm tactics in dealing with
customers whose payments were late.
Thorn said: 'The article relied heavily on anecdotes from former employees,
a number of whom were dismissed for serious breach of company regulations;
all these anecdotes are being investigated.
'It also appears that the views of current management and employees were
either discounted or misrepresented in the article.'
Thorn said Rent-A-Center's goal was continuously to improve relations with
customers.
