<HEADLINE>
FT  29 SEP 93 / Observer: Coffee break
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Visitors to the ludicrously cheap canteen enjoyed by officials at the
International Monetary Fund's Washington headquarters cannot fail to
appreciate the joke of Fund economists who are wont to lecture member
countries across the globe on the infinite virtues of eliminating
market-distorting subsidies.
While the meals remain inexpensive, delegates to this year's annual meeting
detect a welcome move in the direction of pricing transparency. The
coin-operated espresso machine at last reveals the price of a cup - 55
cents; visitors no longer need to contribute to the subsidies by guessing
the wrong amount.
</TEXT>
