FT  29 SEP 93 / People: Hambros
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Lord Kingsdown, the recently ennobled Robin Leigh-Pemberton who retired as
governor of the Bank of England four months ago, is not settling back to
life as a gentleman farmer.
In addition to a directorship at Glaxo, Lord Kingsdown has accepted an
invitation to join the board of HAMBROS, the merchant bank, as a
non-executive director.
How much of a distraction from more gentlemanly pursuits the task will prove
remains to be seen, but with his own secretary and office at his disposal,
he may feel obliged to make fairly regular appearances. 'We look forward to
him contributing in many areas to all the work we will be doing,' says Sir
Adam Ridley, Hambros' PR director.
Lord Kingsdown will take up his appointment, approved at a Hambros board
meeting yesterday, on November 1. His appointment brings the number of
non-executive directors at Hambros to four.
