<HEADLINE>
FT  29 SEP 93 / The Labour Party Conference: Tory broadcast a 'pathetic
trick'
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
LABOUR last night attacked as a 'pathetic trick' a Tory party political
broadcast timed to precede news programmes reporting Mr John Smith's main
conference speech.
The broadcast, featuring a typical couple sitting in front of a blank
television screen, poked fun at the Labour leader, blaming him for the
party's tax policy in the run-up to the last election.
Labour said the broadcast showed the Conservatives were 'running scared'.
</TEXT>
<XX>
