<HEADLINE>
FT  28 SEP 93 / The FT Review of Business Books (28): Insolvency in Europe /
Management
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT RICE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
GUIDE TO INSOLVENCY IN EUROPE by Anthony Houghton and Nigel Atkinson
Deloitte Touche Tohmatsu International/CCH Editions Ltd Pounds 49.50 417
pages
THE NEED for a quick and succinct guide to the insolvency regimes of Europe
can rarely have been greater. Few insolvencies lack an international aspect
these days and professional advisers frequently need to know their way
around the laws and procedures of other European countries when tracing
assets situated there.
Deloittes offers a snapshot of the regimes of the 12 European Community
countries and six East European states, providing basic information on
recovery, rehabilitation, insolvency and debt collection.
Each country is dealt with in the same fashion. There are sections on the
types of business entity; reorganisation procedures; terminal procedures;
types of security and enforcement; debt collection procedures; sources of
law; and sources of information.
The book underlines the lack of harmonisation and limited uniformity between
the insolvency regimes of Europe. It is a handy guide for those wishing to
assess risk, pursue non-payment of debt or make claims in insolvency courts
abroad.
It is only a guide, however, and in most instances there can be no
substitute for taking local advice.
</TEXT>
