<HEADLINE>
FT  28 SEP 93 / The FT Review of Business Books (7): The FT reader -
Economic History
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER MARTIN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE FINANCIAL TIMES GUIDE TO USING THE FINANCIAL PAGES Romesh Vaitilingam
with additional material by Emma Tucker Financial Times/Pitman Pounds
12.95/Pounds 30 216 pages
EVERY DAY, a torrent of financial statistics floods across the pink pages of
the Financial Times. This guide contains an example of every regular table
the paper publishes, with a clear summary of each table's purpose and
sources.
The book provides more than this background information on each table,
however. It also contains a succinct guide to the way the data captured in
the tables reflects the wider forces shaping the activities of economies and
markets. Romesh Vaitilingam, a freelance writer, has managed to steer clear
of financial markets jargon whilst also achieving accuracy and conciseness.
Additional material is provided by Emma Tucker, an economics reporter at the
FT.
Their approach ensures the book's permanence. Even though the format of
individual FT tables changes from time to time, the definitions and insight
the book provides will remain of lasting value to readers.
</TEXT>
