JOHANNESBURG rallied as investors had their first opportunity to respond to
news late on Friday that sanctions were to be lifted following an appeal
from Mr Nelson Mandela, president of the African National Congress, to the
United Nations in New York.
However, some dealers commented that, while hopes for an early merging of
the financial and commercial rands had given shares a boost, the day's gains
