<HEADLINE>
FT  28 SEP 93 / International Capital Markets: CME extends Globex hours
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LAURIE MORSE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   CHICAGO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE Chicago Mercantile Exchange is to extend the time its products are
traded on Globex, the electronic futures and options trading system operated
by Reuters and Chicago's two futures exchanges, writes Laurie Morse in
Chicago.
The longer hours, which take effect on November 1, will eliminate a
late-afternoon pause and bring the system closer to its intended 24-hour
global operation. CME currency and interest rate products will trade
continuously on Globex from early afternoon through to 6am next morning. The
Chicago Board of Trade is not taking part in the move towards 'seamless'
trading.
</TEXT>
