FT  28 SEP 93 / International Company News: Wella takes stake in US
hair-care company
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER PARKES
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   FRANKFURT
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
WELLA, the German personal products specialist, has taken a controlling
stake in Sebastian International, a Los Angeles hair-care company, which
will double its share of the US salon products market to around 8 per cent.
Sebastian, a leading 'designer' brand with a 'trend-setting' environmental
accent, according to Wella, has annual sales of more than Dollars 80m, of
which 18 per cent comes from exports.
The company said it expected turnover in the US from existing activities
this year to reach DM90m (Dollars 55m), compared with total group sales last
year of DM2.75bn.
Neither the size of the holding nor the price paid to the family owners was
disclosed.
The purchase is Wella's second strategically important acquisition this
year. In June it paid DM138m for SmithKline Beecham's Silvikrin, Bristows
and Vosene hair-care brands.
Wella's pre-tax profits for the first half of the current year rose by 3 per
cent to DM66m on turnover up 1.4 per cent to DM1.33bn.
